wiki.content: The Walk Songfacts reports that The Foo Fighters performed this song at the 2012 Grammy Awards. They won five Grammys at the ceremony, including Best Rock Performance and Best Rock Song for this track. wiki.summary: The Walk Songfacts reports that The Foo Fighters performed this song at the 2012 Grammy Awards. They won five Grammys at the ceremony, including Best Rock Performance and Best Rock Song for this track.

track.name: Walk
comments: NOW, FOR THE VERY FIRST TIME <3
LEARNING TO WALK AGAIN I BELIEVE I'VE WAITED LONG ENOUGH WHERE DO I BEGIN?
I think I found my place.....
The last holdouts of a magnificent era!
Dave Grohl is a dude, and the band are great, but they need to stop releasing the same song over and over again. First two albums were magnificent and everything else has been pretty dull.
i like this band but i find some of their songs too repetitive, this is not one of them
he's better in 'them crooked vultures'...this is standard mainstream rock to me

I never wanna die,
I never wanna leave,
I never say goodbye ♫ ♫ ♥
Never knew so much emotion could be channeled into one song.
Saw them in Calgary last year. Epic. This song was unreal.
